# Integration Platforms in Wholesale Operations

## Overview

Integration platforms allow wholesale organizations to connect internal systems with external retailer systems, marketplaces, and logistics platforms.

These platforms enable automated data exchange between organizations and reduce manual order processing.

---

## Purpose

Integration platforms help organizations:

• receive purchase orders electronically  
• transmit shipment notifications  
• send invoices automatically  
• synchronize product and inventory data  

Automation improves operational accuracy and efficiency.

---

## Common Integration Platforms

Examples of commonly used integration platforms include:

• SPS Commerce  
• CommerceHub  
• TrueCommerce  
• EDI VAN providers  
• API integration platforms  

These systems standardize communication between business partners.

---

## Integration Types

Wholesale integrations typically include:

### EDI Integrations

Electronic Data Interchange allows organizations to exchange standardized business documents.

Common transactions include:

• EDI 850 – Purchase Order  
• EDI 855 – Order Acknowledgement  
• EDI 856 – Advance Ship Notice  
• EDI 810 – Invoice

---

### API Integrations

Some organizations use API connections to exchange data between systems in real time.

APIs allow faster synchronization of product data, inventory availability, and order status.

---

## Operational Benefits

Integration platforms allow organizations to:

• reduce manual order entry  
• improve data accuracy  
• accelerate order processing  
• maintain consistent communication with retail partners  

These benefits improve overall operational efficiency.

---

## Final Note

Integration platforms play a critical role in modern wholesale operations. By automating system communication, organizations can process orders faster and maintain reliable operational workflows.
